io.netty.util

Class ByteString

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.netty.util.ByteString
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AsciiString

    public class ByteString
extends Object
    The primary use case for this class is to function as an immutable array of bytes. For performance reasons this class supports sharing memory with external arrays, and also direct access to the underlying memory via array(). Care must be taken when directly accessing the memory as that may invalidate assumptions that this object is immutable.

        public ByteString(ByteBuffer value,
          boolean copy)
